  --decrypted
    - Expected boolean, received string

USAGE
  $ n8n export:credentials

FLAGS
  -h, --help            Show CLI help
  --all                 Export all credentials
  --backup              Sets --all --pretty --separate for simple backups. Only --output has to be set additionally.
  --id <value>          The ID of the credential to export
  -o, --output <value>  Output file name or directory if using separate files
  --pretty              Format the output in an easier to read fashion
  --separate            Exports one file per credential (useful for versioning). Must inform a directory via --output.
  --decrypted           Exports data decrypted / in plain text. ALL SENSITIVE INFORMATION WILL BE VISIBLE IN THE FILES. Use to migrate from a installation to another that have a different secret key (in the config file).

DESCRIPTION
  Export credentials

EXAMPLES
  $ n8n export:credentials --all
  $ n8n export:credentials --id=5 --output=file.json
  $ n8n export:credentials --all --output=backups/latest.json
  $ n8n export:credentials --backup --output=backups/latest/
  $ n8n export:credentials --all --decrypted --output=backups/decrypted.json

